Apr 28 2009 	Really Glad We Stayed Here	We stayed there last Fall for four nights -- our first time in San Francisco (SFO). Sorry it's taken awhile to get this review done -- but I feel compelled to express our very favorable opinion of this facility. We chose this hotel from several possibilities in the area, and are so glad we did. We would definitely go back there again on another visit to SFO.We were on the 7th floor (mid-range price) and had a great view of the Bay &amp; the Bridge (no need to go to a higher floor). Everything in the room was fine -- no complaints -- and the price is right. The beds were just heavenly -- absolutely the best we've had in a hotel, that we can remember. The staff was very helpful and friendly.Our most appreciated service was their restaurant recommendation on the Sunday that we arrived. We wanted something &quot;San Francisco-ish&quot;, but not expensive on this first night -- just a good meal in a relaxed, informal environment. One of the desk ladies suggested &quot;Polkers Gourmet Burgers&quot; up on Polk Street near Russian Hill. And it was great -- just what we wanted: a SFO neighborhood restaurant with good, tasty basic food. We were the only tourists there (amongst many locals) -- we felt like we were definitely in SFO. And in getting there and back to the hotel, we got our first taste of riding the Metro Bus System -- which we found out was easy to use ...... especially since so many bus lines go past or near this Comfort Inn. Did I mention location? This hotel is at a great location -- just perfect, at the corner of Van Ness and Lombard.The breakfast room is very busy in the morning, but also very large, with many tables. It had all that we wanted for breakfast -- very adequate and constantly attended and maintained by more than one person.The only negative is the parking situation -- but that's a negative at almost any SFO hotel, if they even have any. The parking garage is very, very tight -- the ramps and spaces very narrow (and it costs $26 per night). But it's do-able -- and we had an Impala. Unless you're going far from downtown, you won't use your car anyway. The Metro Bus System works just fine, anywhere you want to go in the downtown area.We were very glad that we stayed here -- it felt like home after four nights. &quot;We left our hearts in San Francisco!&quot;	
