Apr 28 2008 	Very Satisfied Third Time Returning Guests	We have yet to be disapointed with our stays at this hotel. It offers quality guest services and amenities; reasonable room and parking rates; staff is knowledgeable and provides excellant services to its valued guests.The parking rate is reasonable compared to other hotels in the area. It has not increased from the $26.00 daily rate which was offered last year with its in and out priveleges. Although parking is very limited; it can be quite a challege to park your vehicle depending on how full the parking lot is at the time. The hotels rooms were recently remodeled with newer furniture and choice bedding. The beds presently have feather topper bed covers. We have stayed on different floors during our three stays. Each time we have found our room to be clean and met the needs of our family. Despite the fact that the bathroom is small, it still met our needs.Walls appear to be thin as voices can be heard from your neighbours as we have experienced during our stay(s). During this past stay, we encountered our neighbour's conversations but this could be in part due to our room being an adjoining room.We have chosen this hotel in part to the fact that it allows five to a room which can be hardship when most hotels only allow 4 guests to a room even though some of those guests are children. We also like the idea, that children under the age of 12 years stay free when sharing a room with their parents as this is the norm for the Choice hotel chain.Another concern is that there are 5 family members and that through out our stay, only 4 sets of towels were left in our room for our family to use.We found it odd that despite the hotel be quieter than on our last visit, our room was not cleaned in a timely manner. We left our room at approx. 9:00 a.m. only to find that when we returned at 3:00 p.m., the room was only being cleaned at that time. We found this to be a bit of an inconvience as we had plans in a couple of our hours and needed to change our clothes to prepare for our outing within two hours.The front desk staff is knowledgeable about the San Francisco area and gladly assists its guests with their requests. We found this to be true on each of our visits especially when it came to using the transit system. This hotel offers a complimentary breakfast daily with a good variety of hot and cold items. The staff that maintains the breakfast should be rewarded for their excellant service. They continually ensure that items are always on hand, dishes are available and that the tables are clean for the guests of the hotel.The location of this hotel is close to many areas of interest: Fisherman's Wharf, Ghirardelli Square and Lombard Street and are all within a 15 minute walk from the hotel. If wanting to visit other areas such as Chinatown and AT&amp;T park, transit stops are close by within a few blocks of the hotel.We made reservations for a room located on the middle floors. After making our reservation, we had an inquiry and contacted the hotel. It was during the course of our conversation, that the front desk reservation staff discovered that we were returning guests to the hotel and due to the hotel having vacancies on the upper floors, much to our surprise the staff decided on its own to upgrade our room to a full view room located on the 10th floor in appreciation that we were returning guests at no extra cost to us.The Comfort Inn By The Bay has yet to disappoint us during our stay(s) and we highly recommend this hotel to anyone that will be visiting San Francisco.	
Apr 26 2008 	Made Our Stay a Great One!	A REAL hotel (not a noisy motor lodge) with excellent friendly staff, a comfortable lobby, a convenient free lite-breakfast buffet, and a super location near Fisherman's Wharf (but away from the noise and bustle), and close to public transportation. Do yourself a BIG favor and book an odd-numbered room on a high floor. The expansive view from your own room of the Golden Gate Bridge and the Marin Highlands and the Bay full of boats and windsurfers will be one of the highlights of your trip--and the upgrade will cost you less than most tours. Another good investment is a multi-day public transportation pass, useable on all trolleys and buses (available at the trolley stop at Beach &amp; Hyde. Pay $3 more for a map of the system.) DO use the buses and trolleys to take you UP the hills. Our favorite places: Muir Woods, Coit Tower (check out the view and WPA murals), the Ferry Terminal (full of cafes, bread, wine, cheese and chocolate shops), the Maritime Museum on Hyde St. Pier (go down into the Balclutha and see how the Captain and the poor Chinese sailors lived), North Beach (great restaurants and cafes), the trolley rides, and, yes, the sea lions on Pier 39. Skip Chinatown. Have Fun!	
Apr 21 2008 	Comfort Inn by the Bay	I recently had a four night stay at the Comfort Inn by the Bay and was very pleased with the quality of the accomodations for the price. The hotel is situated on Van Ness and is approximately a 15 minute walk from the wharf, so it was a good starting point for seeing the wharf, alcatraz, ghiradelli square, and Lombard. It is near a few bus lines, which we used to go to a baseball game, and within a ten minute walk or so of the cable cars. We did find that it is far enough from the BART station that a cab is required to take public transport to the airport, however (although there may be a bus that runs there). The rooms were very clean, and the interior decorations (bedspreads, carpets, etc) seemed fairly new. The only downside to the room was the bathroom. The tub/shower and toilet were in separate room (vanity on the outside) that was extremely cramped and the tub/shower curtains, etc. could have used an update. Other than that, we were very pleased with the accomodation for the price (we also had a great view of the golden gate bridge from our window) and enjoyed the free breakfast. The only other thing I would mention is that while there were a few places to eat near the hotel, the areas that had a lot of restaurants and nightlife were at least a 10-15 minute walk, which might be a consideration if you tend to stay out late and would like to be able to walk back to the hotel.	
