Jan 24 2008 	Friendly staff and good location	Really enjoyed my stay! The staff was very friendly and helped out however they could. Their was a large group of Australian teenagers staying on &quot;holiday&quot; when we were there, but the staff helped us get the parking garage by opening a secret door every morning when we were leaving. The breakfast is nothing to write home about, muffins, waffles, english muffins, fruit, pastries, and juice, but the waffles were good. The rooms were nice, not large, but not tiny. I opted not to pay extra for a bayside room since I was working all day and did not get to enjoy the view. One of the other people in my group did stay in one of the bay rooms and I would recommend it if you are on vacation.My only complaints would be:1. 29.65 for parking, good god! I would suggest not getting a car if you are staying in the bay area because public transportation works fine to get around.2. One of the elevators kept breaking, which was a headache in the morning.I would stay here again if I am in San Fran.	
