 - walked across the street to the store and purchased some drinks.The breakfast room was pretty good - a good assortment of fresh fruit,danish,muffins,hard boiled eggs ,tea,coffee,juice and waffles,never had a problem finding a table to eat at but after 8am it got quite busy.We saw alot of the city in 4 days - Alcatraz is amazing , Fisherman's Wharf was also a fave -- so much going on there and some great food available - we really liked eating at Nick's Lighthouse , the seafood there was awesome. Rented a car and drove to Napa and Sonoma valley - went to a winery called Rosso &amp; Bianco, it is owned by Francis Ford Coppola and it was absolutely amazing ! You could sit on the terrace and have lunch,or for $10 you could do a little wine sampling which was nice , the gardens are well kept and so pretty .We also did the double decker bus tour in the evening for $15 a person ,well worth it as we were able to get some fantastic pictures - a great way to see the city! I would definately go back as 4 days was just not enough to see everything, however - I would try a different hotel next time , the people running this hotel didn't seem to really know what they were doing . feel free to contact me at debrab60@hotmail.com if u have any questions.	
