Oct 24 2007 	No frills honeymoon in SFO	My husband and I stayed here for our honeymoon. Had a 10th floor room with a bay/bridge view. Room had in-room fridge and safe. Worth the extra $20 bucks or so a night if you are staying for multiple nights. The bridge view is great, but the bay view is just ok because some developer built a couple matching eyesores that block most of the view of Alcatraz. Speaking of Alcatraz, you can still see the lighthouse and it is bright enough to shine into the room at night--not in an annoying, keep you awake kind of way, but a hey, that's Alcatraz kind of way. Excellent access to public transportation and walking distance to the junk filled shops of Fisherman's Wharf. The breakfast area is very busy in the morning, so get down there by 7:45 or be prepared wait for a table to eat. Pretty good breakfast--make your own waffles, boiled eggs, cereal, bagels, apples, oranges, etc.	
Oct 22 2007 	Walking distance to Fisherman's Wharf	This was our first stop on a 2 week trip to northern California. The first 2 nights we had a room facing another tall building, but the next 2 nights we upgraded to a Bay view room with a fantastic vista including the Golden Gate bridge and Alcatraz island. They let us store our luggage in their office while we continued our touring of the City.The included continental breakfast was better than most mid-range hotels. Three of the four front desk staff that we talked with were VERY helpful in providing directions, suggesting restaurants, reimbursing us for lost money in the soda machine, etc. The 4th clerk acted like he hated his job - so we avoided talking with him.It is good that we did not yet have a car, because parking in the hotel's basement garage is very expensive. But when we picked up our rental car to start on the remainder of our vacation, the staff let us park for free while we loaded our luggage.The famous twisted road on Lombard Street is only 3 blocks from the hotel - but it is like walking up a cliff at almost a 30% slope! We learned that the frequent buses on Van Ness Avenue in front of the hotel will get you almost anywhere in the City with ease, and for only $1.50. Definitely worth it to save your legs on the hills.	
